      "description": "This E46 M3 is powered by the high-strung S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. The powertrain is mated to a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission, delivering torque through a factory M Variable Differential Lock. To ensure chassis longevity, the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance. The suspension retains its original geometry with refreshed bushings, providing the precise turn-in and communicative steering feedback these cars are known for. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with its mileage, the mechanical vitals are in excellent health, with a recently overhauled cooling system and a clean DME scan. A mechanically sound example of an analog performance icon.",
